t consumption and\n'handle other freight at the sain\ntime without s'gns of distress.\"\nThe situation, of course, the report\ninsists, turns upon rhe present price\nof coal, the consumer insisting that\nit should come down and the opera 1-\n\u2018lown Hs far as it\ns The report com'nines\n\u201cBuy when needed may prove too\nconservative advice at this time. The\n\u25a0\u25a0consumer waiting for low prices and\ntlie producer delaying price adjusi\niiient might he found equally respon\nsildc for tine uneconomic seasonal\nI fluctuation in the coal output. Buy\nonly as needed' may result in cheap\ncr coal in the bin. hut the bin may\n'he too nearly empty most of the time\nwhen the need is greatest.\u201d\ni\nSISTERS DIE FROM CRASH\nGirls of 11 and 9 Victims When Train\nStrikes Stalled Auto.\ni Betiovo. I\u2019a.. March -S. Margaret\nI Brown, aged years, who wtts injttr\ned w hen her sister. Bessie, aged 11.\nj was killed as the automobile in w hich\ni they were riding stalled in front of\nI the Buffalo Fixer on the IVnnsylva\nnia railroad at the North Bend cross\ni ing. died at the Renovo Hospital.\nThe two girls were accompanied hy\ntheir F/,rr. Harry Brown, of Sonlli\nj Renovo. and an older daughter. An\nnette, who occupied the from sea!\nami escaped hy jumping. The injur\ned girls were placed in a truck and\nstarted for the hospital, hut Bessie\ndied on the way and Margaret a few\nhours later.\nGOLD FIND IN ALASKA\nMiners on Cocomo Creek Claim to\nHave Hit Paying Streak.\nFairbanks, Alaska, March Us. This\ncity is enjoying its first real mining\nsensation in years with the discovery\nof gold on t\u2019oeomo (\u2019reek, within\nthree miles of town.\nThe pay streak runs five dollars a\nwindlass bucket, according to Han\nl and .lack Grittiti and .Tames Gorham,\nowners of the claim. The streak is\nsaid to he several feet wide. 'Phis\nis the lirst time gold has Iteea found\non Cocomo Creek since prospecting\nstarted there in 1910.\n\nLives Over Century to Die in Well.\