profits on a ris- J\ning market, and if they can\u2019t take\ntheir medicine now during the per- 1\niod of re-adjustment, it\u2019s a queer\nthing.\nThat is what the Retailers think. J\nAnd if Hie Retailers, who have\nworn out their pencils marking up\nprices can\u2019t make the necessary re-\nduct tons now without whimpering.\nthey would belter shut up shop.\nThat is what the Manufacturers J\nand Wholesalers say.\nYou have been having a chance to J\nmake and save a little money for i\nseveral years, and if you can\u2019t stand 1\na little hard time you\u2019re either a\npretty poor sport or you\u2019re a pretty\npoor business man.\nThat is what Everybody says to\nEverybody else. 1\nAnd what Everybody says must 1\nbe so! j\n\u2014FARM LIFE. f\nGETTING EVEN\nSimpkins had taken his wife and\nher mother to the sea shore. On\nthe last day of (heir vacation the old\nlady disappeared beneath the briney.\nbillows. Being unable to remain\nlonger from his business, simpkins\nleft word with the beach authorities\nto wire him if the body were recov\nered, and returned to the city. Two\ndays later came a telegram; \u201cBody\nwashed ashore, completely covered\nwith lobsters.\u201d\nSimpkins wired back: \u201cShip lob\nsters by freight, ray expense. Re\nset halt.\u201d- \u2014Agency Bulletin.\nI SEI.ESS CHANGE\nA woebegone looking traveler In a j\nsmall Georgia town approached the!\nancient Negro who operated the one\ni car ferry accross a dinky stream,\ni and accosted him with:\n\"Uncle. I\u2019m broke and I got to\nget across the river. Will you\ntrust me for it?\u201d\n\"Fare's only 3 cents, boss.\u201d\nUncle Mose placidly resumed his\npipiN\n\u201cBoss,\u201d he ef yo am t\ni got 3 cents you won\u2019t be no better\noff on dat side de ribber dan you\u2019 is\non dis.\u201d I\n1\nJ\\ KI'KRCT FEBRUARY I. I2t\nLeave Claiborne Hatty except Sunday j*\n10:00 A. XI. i\nLcax\u2019e Annapolis Hatty except Sunday\ns:go I*. XI. I\nKKIIIAVS\nLeave Claiborne 7:15 r. XI., in addition\nto